sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1392970
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: For this part an artifical Terminator is used (generally added to another parts). The promoter is a TetR repressible promoter.It is sequenced for pTet inverting regulator. Promoter is constitutively ON and repressed by TetR. TetR repression is inhibited by the addition of tetracycline or its analog part
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Şeniz Y??ksel
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Enterobacteria phage T4 http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/viewer.fcgi?val=29366675&from=66503&to=66997&view=gbwithparts modified E. coli thr terminator, replaced all A-T pairs in stem with C-G pairs BiblioPlus Extension Error fetching PMID 9092630:
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Bidirectional, with the reverse estimated to be more effective than the forward. Has a polyA tail of 9 residues. High expression of lysozyme only is toxic to bacteria. BBa_R0040 (TetR repressible promoter) is based on a cI promoter. It has been modified to include two TetR binding sites. Constructed by DNA synthesis.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B1006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Artificial terminator, estimated %T~>90% *8bp stem, 6nt loop *Bidirectional, estimated reverse %T~>90%

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: modified E. coli thr terminator, replaced all A-T pairs in stem with C-G pairs

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: p(tetR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence for pTet inverting regulator driven by the TetR protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lutz, R., Bujard, H., Nucleic Acids Research (1997) 25, 1203-1210.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_R0040 TetR-Regulated Promoter is based on a cI promoter. It has been modified to include two TetR binding sites and the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites.
